Infinity Taxi
Project Description

Infinity Taxi is a taxi dispatch and tracking system built using FastAPI, SQLite, Pydantic, and Streamlit. The application allows customers to request rides, choose available drivers, track driver locations on a live map, and monitor ride progress in real time.

The system includes an admin dashboard for managing drivers and rides, as well as a customer interface for requesting and tracking trips. Driver availability, ride statuses, estimated arrival times, and fares are automatically managed by the application.

Running the Project
1. Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
2. Create the Database

If a taxi.db file already exists and you want a fresh database, delete it first.

Then run:

python database.py
3. Start the FastAPI Backend

Open a terminal and run:

uvicorn main:app --reload

You can verify that the API is running by opening:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
4. Start the Streamlit Application

Open a second terminal and run:

streamlit run app.py

The Infinity Taxi dashboard should now open in your browser.
